    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Mounting Engine on Stand - Component
        Removal - Oil System Module
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Oil System Module</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove one bolt (M8 x 16) securing oil cooling drain tube assembly to crankcase.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove eight bolts (M8 x 30) securing oil system module to crankcase.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove oil system module and oil cooler drain tube as an assembly from crankcase and discard
                O-rings. The oil cooler drain tube is trapped between the oil system module and the front cover.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
